Material Information Summary

Exploration Results Announcement – Mankayan Copper-Gold Project, Philippines

  • High-grade surface samples confirmed with assays up to 6 g/t Au and 1.9% Cu (e.g., Sample CS-4: 5.97 g/t Au, 1.9% Cu, 53.1 g/t Ag).
  • Recent drill results:
  • BRC60: 432m @ 1.25% CuEq (0.55% Cu, 0.89 g/t Au) from 692m, including 210m @ 1.60% CuEq (0.69% Cu, 1.16 g/t Au).
  • Ongoing exploration: Mapping/sampling program initiated to define new targets near the Mankayan deposit.
  • Post-merger position: $22.6M capital raised (previously disclosed) to fund exploration. Maiden drill program commencing soon.

No material changes to Mineral Resources; JORC 2012 assumptions remain unchanged.

(Note: This is a discovery/exploration update; no new capital raising, financials, or immediate catalysts beyond exploration progress.)

Material Information Summary

Exploration Update Announcement

  • Project: Leonora Goldfields Project (LGP), WA – wholly owned by Evergreen Lithium (ASX:EG1).
  • Resource: 63,000oz Au JORC 2012 Inferred Resource (Craig’s Rest: 48,600oz, Victor Bore: 11,700oz, Great Northern: 2,700oz).
  • High-Grade Intercepts:
  • 5m at 57.9 g/t Au (Tarmoola RAB hole).
  • 2m at 26.6 g/t Au (Tarmoola RC hole).
  • Upcoming Drilling Campaign: Targets Craig’s Rest, Victor Bore, Great Northern to expand/upgrade resource.
  • Strategic Advantages:
  • Proximity to two large-scale gold processing plants (<40km).
  • 15 tenements (13 mining/prospecting, 1 exploration).

Next Steps

  • Regulatory approvals and contractor finalisation for drilling.
  • Conversion of five prospecting licences to mining leases (submissions initiated by prior owner).

No capital raising, financials, or material corporate changes disclosed.

Priority Note: Focus on high-grade potential and near-term drilling, but resource remains early-stage (Inferred). Infrastructure proximity mitigates development risk.

Note: Subject to regulatory approvals. Non-binding cost estimate. No immediate capital raising or trading halt required.

Here is the concise summary of material information from the ASX announcement:

Key Highlights:

  • Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE): 953koz gold @ 2.4g/t Au (cut-off: 1g/t).
  • Exploration Upside: Only 21,500m of drilling completed so far (90% focused on Main Zone). Newly identified Doyles fold (500m west of Main Zone) has potential to expand MRE.
  • Recent Drill Results:
  • SC108/SC109 intersected arsenopyrite veining and gold mineralization 200m below prior drilling.
  • SC109 returned 4m @ 2.3g/t Au, suggesting increasing mineralization at depth.
  • Near-Term Catalysts:
  • Mining permit decision expected by end of 2025.
  • Infill drilling (to upgrade Inferred to Indicated MRE) targeted for completion by Q2 2026.
  • Updated MRE and Scoping Study to be released in Q3 2026.
  • Strategic Outlook: Potential to access new mineralization (Doyles, Western Outcrops, Anvil) via centralized underground development, enhancing project economics.

No capital raising or financial data disclosed.
No material operational updates beyond exploration progress.

Orthocell Limited – Quarterly Report (June 2025) – Material Summary

Financial Highlights

  • Revenue:
  • Quarterly: $2.73m (up 22.8% QoQ, 45.1% YoY)
  • FY2025: $9.19m (up 35.8% YoY) – fifth consecutive quarterly record.
  • Compound Quarterly Growth Rate (CQGR): 9.5% over 3 years.
  • Cash Position: $28.6m (no debt), up 38.8% YoY.

Key Operational Developments

  1. Remplir™ (Nerve Repair Product):
  2. FDA 510(k) clearance (April 2025); initial US rollout underway.
  3. First US surgical use completed; distributor network established (14 distributors across 25 states).
  4. Additional approvals in Hong Kong, Thailand, Canada.

  5. US market potential: $1.6bn.

  6. Striate+™ (Dental Membrane):

  7. Regulatory approval in Brazil (annual market opportunity: $65m).
  8. Global distribution via BioHorizons; launches planned in Germany/Austria/Switzerland.

Cash Flow & Liquidity

  • Net operating outflow: $3.54m (quarter), $8.51m (FY2025).
  • Funding runway: 8.09 quarters based on current cash reserves.

Upcoming Catalyst

  • Expected US sales ramp for Remplir in 1H FY26.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Results (High-Grade Gold Intersections)

  • 6m @ 2.98 g/t Au from 76m (GUYAC0135), incl. 4m @ 4.35 g/t Au

  • Initial $5M spend by GOR underway; RC drilling scheduled for mid-July 2025 to follow up AC results.

Next Steps

  • RC drilling program planned to test primary gold zones beneath high-grade AC anomalies.
